WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.330
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 02
"Redial"

2
00:00:07.330 --> 00:00:08.450
[BOMB BEEPING]
- Is that a...?

3
00:00:08.450 --> 00:00:08.990
Yeah.

4
00:00:08.990 --> 00:00:10.570
Do you know how to...?
- No.

5
00:00:11.300 --> 00:00:12.350
[PASSENGERS SCREAMING]

6
00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:16.560
[ ♪ OMINOUS MUSIC ♪ ]

7
00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:20.310
You pay your dues in Night Action. you put your time in in that room...

8
00:00:20.310 --> 00:00:23.230
manning a phone that never rings. and better things will come your way.

9
00:00:23.230 --> 00:00:26.860
But you need more than just me to sign off
on a promotion. You need Hawkins too.

10
00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:28.190
HAWKINS: You report to us both.

11
00:00:28.190 --> 00:00:30.200
You've forgotten that half of the equation.

12
00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:32.410
I need to personally file for bankruptcy.

13
00:00:32.410 --> 00:00:35.990
After the data breach. the ransomware. all my clients bailed.

14
00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:37.700
You can stay here as long as you need.

15
00:00:39.120 --> 00:00:41.170
ROSE: What's happening?
- Someone is outside.

16
00:00:41.170 --> 00:00:43.170
Call this number. say "Night Action."

17
00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:47.760
[ROSE GASPING]

18
00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:49.010
[PHONE RINGING]

19
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:53.590
Night Action.
- Deputy Director Hawkins.

20
00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:55.550
HAWKINS: What are you doing here?

21
00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:58.470
Diane Farr sent me to take Miss Larkin.
- HAWKINS: Take her where?

22
00:00:58.480 --> 00:00:59.930
ROSE: Who do you work for?
- FBI.

23
00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:01.440
They're after me now. aren't they?

24
00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:04.150
What I can tell you are my orders. which are to protect you.

25
00:01:04.150 --> 00:01:06.110
So my aunt and uncle were spies?

26
00:01:06.110 --> 00:01:09.110
I'm as low-level as it gets in the White House.

27
00:01:09.110 --> 00:01:10.740
Trust me. I... I don't know anything.

28
00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:14.620
MAN: Found it!

29
00:01:16.120 --> 00:01:17.910
PETER: Tell them the truth about what you saw.

30
00:01:17.910 --> 00:01:20.870
My aunt said there's someone in the White House who can't be trusted.

31
00:01:20.870 --> 00:01:23.330
We wanna make this as comfortable for you as possible.

32
00:01:23.330 --> 00:01:26.250
Have a seat. Miss Larkin. We have a lot to go over.

33
00:01:26.930 --> 00:01:39.440
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 02
"Redial"

34
00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:40.820
[PHONE RINGING ECHOING]

35
00:01:42.980 --> 00:01:44.350
WOMAN: How many employees?

36
00:01:44.350 --> 00:01:46.650
37 now. 80 by the end of the year.

37
00:01:46.650 --> 00:01:49.020
On track for 200 by 3ʳᵈ quarter next year.

38
00:01:49.030 --> 00:01:50.610
WOMAN: Ready for that kind of growth?

39
00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:51.860
We're actually taking it slow.

40
00:01:51.860 --> 00:01:54.570
We turn down four clients for every one we take on.

41
00:01:54.570 --> 00:01:56.820
Where do you see the cybersecurity sector trending?

42
00:01:56.830 --> 00:01:58.950
Right now large companies have sensitive information...

43
00:01:58.950 --> 00:01:59.950
they need to protect...

44
00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:04.290
but smaller companies. individuals. privacy is important to them too.

45
00:02:04.290 --> 00:02:06.790
Silicon Valley can be brutal on women.

46
00:02:06.790 --> 00:02:11.210
You're a rare female CEO not working in the beauty or wellness space.

47
00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:14.550
What made you think you could succeed where many women hit roadblocks?

48
00:02:14.550 --> 00:02:16.050
I'm so sorry.

49
00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:17.550
Uh. there's a call.

50
00:02:17.550 --> 00:02:18.680
Uh. can it wait?

51
00:02:19.350 --> 00:02:20.260
Who is it?

52
00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:21.600
It's Lawrence Finster.

53
00:02:22.180 --> 00:02:23.810
Oh. our biggest account.

54
00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:25.690
Sorry.
- WOMAN: No problem.

55
00:02:25.690 --> 00:02:27.020
Here?
- Just there.

56
00:02:27.690 --> 00:02:29.020
[PHONES RINGING]

57
00:02:31.570 --> 00:02:33.360
Mr. Finster. it's Rose Larkin. How can I...?

58
00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:35.360
LAWRENCE: <i>Someone's in our goddamn system.</i>

59
00:02:35.360 --> 00:02:38.870
<i>We're completely locked out. Everything's shut down.</i>

60
00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:40.870
Um. sorry. what's going on?

61
00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:43.040
LAWRENCE: <i>The hackers just contacted us.</i>

62
00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:45.080
<i>They want 7.2 million in Bitcoin...</i>

63
00:02:45.080 --> 00:02:48.040
<i>or they release our proprietary technology online...</i>

64
00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:49.000
<i>which will sink us.</i>

65
00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:50.790
There must be some mistake.

66
00:02:50.800 --> 00:02:51.920
Uh. one second.

67
00:02:52.420 --> 00:02:54.090
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

68
00:02:55.470 --> 00:02:56.470
Sorry. Excuse me.

69
00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:00.720
[ROSE BREATHING HEAVILY]

70
00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:01.720
[LOCK DISENGAGING]

71
00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:04.390
Khadim.
- I know. I'm trying.

72
00:03:04.390 --> 00:03:05.890
Someone's fucked with the code.

73
00:03:05.890 --> 00:03:06.810
On our end?

74
00:03:06.810 --> 00:03:08.900
It doesn't make sense. Who'd do this?

75
00:03:08.900 --> 00:03:10.190
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

76
00:03:11.570 --> 00:03:13.070
Fuck. it's Adam.

77
00:03:13.070 --> 00:03:13.990
Let me in.

78
00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:21.490
Adam. what did you do? Look.

79
00:03:25.660 --> 00:03:27.500
[ ♪ OPENING THEME MUSIC ♪ ]

80
00:03:28.040 --> 00:03:31.420
HAWKINS: <i>We've been at this for hours. Just tell us the truth already.</i>

81
00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:33.710
What more do you want from me?
- Actual help.

82
00:03:33.710 --> 00:03:36.010
You said on the phone call that you saw his face.

83
00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:38.010
I saw his figure. not his face.

84
00:03:38.010 --> 00:03:39.430
You said you saw his face.

85
00:03:39.430 --> 00:03:41.890
Well. that was a mistake. Maybe I was in shock.

86
00:03:41.890 --> 00:03:43.760
HAWKINS: How tall was he? What was his build?

87
00:03:43.770 --> 00:03:45.560
White. Black. Hispanic?

88
00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:46.520
Nothing?

89
00:03:47.020 --> 00:03:47.890
Jesus.

90
00:03:47.890 --> 00:03:50.020
How do we know that you aren't in on this?

91
00:03:50.020 --> 00:03:51.400
Jamie. that's ridiculous.

92
00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:53.900
Her aunt and uncle are killed. and she didn't get a scratch?

93
00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:54.940
Stop it.

94
00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:57.740
Look. I don't really believe that you're involved with this...

95
00:03:57.740 --> 00:04:00.200
but I don't think you're being honest with me either.

96
00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:02.450
Do you wanna find your aunt and uncle's killer or not?

97
00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:04.910
Of course I do. but that's your goddamn job.

98
00:04:04.910 --> 00:04:08.080
Mine is to plan a double funeral for the only family I had left.

99
00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:09.540
Rose. we're on the same side.

100
00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:10.750
Well. tell that asshole.

101
00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:13.840
And someone's still trying to kill me. Do something about that.

102
00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:19.630
What's. uh. what's going on?

103
00:04:20.340 --> 00:04:21.260
She's hiding something.

104
00:04:21.260 --> 00:04:22.930
She's endured something terrible.

105
00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:24.100
Yes. she has.

106
00:04:24.890 --> 00:04:27.220
But she's hiding something.
- How do you know. sir?

107
00:04:27.230 --> 00:04:29.140
30 years as a federal Agent. that's how.

108
00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:32.270
Tell me you didn't see it.

109
00:04:34.980 --> 00:04:36.360
Maybe you can get her to talk.

110
00:04:40.070 --> 00:04:41.410
So. what happens now?

111
00:04:41.410 --> 00:04:45.120
We have a car with Secret Service Agents
who'll take you to the Remborne Hotel.

112
00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:48.080
You'll remain under their protection until it's safe to go home.

113
00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:51.160
I'll walk. I could use the air.
- That's not going to work.

114
00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:54.090
Well. unless you're planning to arrest me. it's gonna have to.

115
00:04:54.590 --> 00:04:55.670
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

116
00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:59.970
I'll... I'll just escort her. and the Agents can. uh. trail behind us.

117
00:05:01.550 --> 00:05:05.050
Sutherland does not have the training to work a witness...

118
00:05:05.050 --> 00:05:07.260
and we don't have time to fix things when he fucks up.

119
00:05:07.270 --> 00:05:10.100
Just because you underestimate him. doesn't mean I do.

120
00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:13.310
I've spent the last year watching him. He can do this.

121
00:05:14.940 --> 00:05:17.030
Or are you afraid he'll succeed where you couldn't?

122
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:20.860
So you didn't tell them what you saw?

123
00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:22.320
No. You know why.

124
00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:24.780
What's your plan here. Rose?

125
00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.120
To stay alive as long as possible.

126
00:05:29.410 --> 00:05:31.120
What didn't you tell them exactly?

127
00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:33.210
What. you don't trust me now?

128
00:05:33.920 --> 00:05:36.170
To a point. but someone in the White House wants me dead.

129
00:05:36.170 --> 00:05:37.750
What if you misheard?
- [ROSE SCOFFING]

130
00:05:37.750 --> 00:05:39.710
Or she was wrong? Give them a description.

131
00:05:39.710 --> 00:05:42.050
If the people behind this know I can ID one of the killers...

132
00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:43.470
how safe do you think I'll be?

133
00:05:44.390 --> 00:05:47.300
You believe in your bosses so much. go ahead. tell them I lied.

134
00:05:47.310 --> 00:05:48.470
See what happens.

135
00:05:49.060 --> 00:05:50.810
It's only my life at stake.

136
00:05:50.810 --> 00:05:51.980
Maybe yours too now.

137
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:02.950
Okay. this is it. so...

138
00:06:03.610 --> 00:06:05.070
Just stay off that balcony.

139
00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.070
And. uh...

140
00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.370
generally. just try to stay out of sight. okay?

141
00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:12.040
Please.

142
00:06:12.750 --> 00:06:14.120
So it's like a jail cell?

143
00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:16.040
PETER: What? No.

144
00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:18.710
No. Order anything you want from room service.

145
00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:20.670
Uh. you got a minibar.

146
00:06:20.670 --> 00:06:24.170
And you got 2 Secret Service Agents in the hall. 4 in the lobby.

147
00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:25.380
It's gonna be fine.

148
00:06:25.390 --> 00:06:26.470
ROSE: Some life.

149
00:06:26.470 --> 00:06:29.680
No laptop. no books to read. Just stuck here.

150
00:06:31.180 --> 00:06:32.520
Work on your pool game.

151
00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:35.810
Is that gonna be my new career?
- What. a 9-ball hustler?

152
00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.690
Enough practice. maybe. Who knows?

153
00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:39.650
You can do it.

154
00:06:43.190 --> 00:06:44.320
Hey.

155
00:06:45.110 --> 00:06:46.490
We're gonna get these guys...

156
00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:48.070
believe me.

157
00:06:48.570 --> 00:06:50.410
You need anything else before I go?

158
00:06:51.490 --> 00:06:52.830
Wait. you're not staying?

159
00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:55.000
I have to go to work.

160
00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:56.870
But you work nights.

161
00:06:56.870 --> 00:06:58.960
Farr wanted my help on this. so...

162
00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.210
So that's it?

163
00:07:00.210 --> 00:07:02.460
Just goodbye forever?

164
00:07:05.130 --> 00:07:06.930
I don't know. Maybe.

165
00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:11.180
These Secret Service guys. they're gonna be a lot better...

166
00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:12.930
at protecting you than I am.

167
00:07:14.680 --> 00:07:15.600
You did okay.

168
00:07:16.690 --> 00:07:18.770
Thanks. You did okay too.

169
00:07:20.310 --> 00:07:21.610
Thank you.
- PETER: Yeah.

170
00:07:27.320 --> 00:07:28.280
[DOOR OPENING]

171
00:07:30.780 --> 00:07:31.620
Um...

172
00:07:32.450 --> 00:07:34.660
you guys take care of her. okay?

173
00:07:34.660 --> 00:07:35.580
Of course.

174
00:07:36.540 --> 00:07:38.170
PETER: Thank you.
- MAN: You got it.

175
00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:39.830
[ELEVATOR CHIMING]

176
00:07:40.540 --> 00:07:42.550
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [PHONES RINGING]

177
00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:02.690
Hey. Uh. can you deliver these to room 610. please?

178
00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:04.440
MAN: Right away.
- Thanks.

179
00:08:05.740 --> 00:08:07.440
Can you tell her they're from Peter?

180
00:08:07.450 --> 00:08:08.360
Will do.

181
00:08:08.360 --> 00:08:10.450
[ ♪ ROCK MUSIC ♪ ]

182
00:08:11.200 --> 00:08:13.660
♪ You better believe in karma ♪♪

183
00:08:14.370 --> 00:08:16.040
I wonder what's in the bag.

184
00:08:17.910 --> 00:08:19.160
You're not curious?

185
00:08:19.170 --> 00:08:21.630
No. I used to be a curious person...

186
00:08:21.630 --> 00:08:25.760
but I learned quickly that some things are better left alone.

187
00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:29.220
What's something you used to be curious about?

188
00:08:30.220 --> 00:08:31.930
When you'd come into my life.

189
00:08:33.470 --> 00:08:35.100
What?
- Come on. tell me.

190
00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:36.180
Uh...

191
00:08:36.970 --> 00:08:41.150
why people behave in opposition to their best interests.

192
00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:43.310
What'd you decide?

193
00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:45.900
That people... [SIGHING]

194
00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:48.990
they need risk in their lives to feel something...

195
00:08:48.990 --> 00:08:50.240
[POLICE SIREN CHIRPING]

196
00:08:50.240 --> 00:08:51.280
...different.

197
00:08:52.370 --> 00:08:53.820
How fast were you going?

198
00:08:54.530 --> 00:08:55.490
Fast.

199
00:08:57.160 --> 00:08:58.870
I was trying to get us there.

200
00:08:58.870 --> 00:09:00.710
Just pull over slowly. okay?

201
00:09:10.090 --> 00:09:12.050
[INDISTINCT POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

202
00:09:12.050 --> 00:09:14.090
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

203
00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:15.140
MAN: Whoa.

204
00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:16.600
Just in case.

205
00:09:17.470 --> 00:09:21.980
License and registration are both clean.
so just smile and take your ticket. okay?

206
00:09:30.950 --> 00:09:32.990
I was speeding wasn't I. Officer?

207
00:09:34.990 --> 00:09:36.990
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

208
00:09:47.130 --> 00:09:48.000
MAN: Thanks.

209
00:09:48.590 --> 00:09:49.550
[SCANNER TRILLING]

210
00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:51.630
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

211
00:09:52.430 --> 00:09:54.010
MAN: Uh. sir. your key.

212
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:54.970
Thank you.

213
00:09:55.470 --> 00:09:56.680
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGING]

214
00:10:02.890 --> 00:10:04.600
How's Rose?
- She's fine.

215
00:10:04.600 --> 00:10:06.440
DIANE: You get anything more out of her?

216
00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:07.690
Nothing new. no.

217
00:10:07.690 --> 00:10:09.610
[PETER SIGHING]
- That's Hawkins' chair.

218
00:10:09.610 --> 00:10:11.240
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

219
00:10:11.990 --> 00:10:12.950
PETER: Sorry. sir.

220
00:10:15.950 --> 00:10:19.330
Fourteen hours since Emma and Henry Campbell were killed.

221
00:10:19.330 --> 00:10:22.200
The President wants to know what we know. So. what do we know?

222
00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:24.460
Investigation is proceeding.

223
00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:28.170
I'm not a fucking <i>Washington Post</i> reporter. Don't spin me.

224
00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:34.220
The Campbells worked for us in counterintelligence.

225
00:10:34.220 --> 00:10:36.800
Mostly recruiting foreign assets domestically.

226
00:10:36.800 --> 00:10:38.390
But they retired a few years ago.

227
00:10:38.390 --> 00:10:40.930
The fact that they had their niece call Night Action...

228
00:10:40.930 --> 00:10:42.770
means they were working off the books.

229
00:10:42.770 --> 00:10:45.560
The Campbells make any enemies when they were working for the FBI?

230
00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:47.850
No one that would do this to them.
- How do you know?

231
00:10:47.860 --> 00:10:50.320
'Cause that's not how the game is played in spy land.

232
00:10:50.320 --> 00:10:51.400
MAN: Spy land?

233
00:10:51.400 --> 00:10:54.950
Well. maybe someone changed the rules in spy land?

234
00:10:55.530 --> 00:10:57.700
What about surveillance footage near their house?

235
00:10:57.700 --> 00:10:58.950
Nothing helpful.

236
00:10:58.950 --> 00:11:00.700
So the bureau's nowhere?

237
00:11:00.700 --> 00:11:03.700
Maybe Secret Service needs to step in more.

238
00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:04.830
Maybe.
- MAN#2: Hmm.

239
00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:08.420
You stay on your own turf there. buddy boy. FBI's got a handle on this.

240
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:09.710
Just no suspects.

241
00:11:11.250 --> 00:11:14.210
I'd like to take another crack at the girl. see what she's hiding.

242
00:11:14.220 --> 00:11:16.260
Don't you think she's been traumatized enough. sir?

243
00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:19.090
It's called conducting an investigation. Sutherland.

244
00:11:19.100 --> 00:11:21.890
And you're lucky you're even invited up here with the grown-ups.

245
00:11:21.890 --> 00:11:24.970
Your prize witness wouldn't be alive if it weren't for him.

246
00:11:24.980 --> 00:11:27.690
What else aren't you sharing about your investigation?

247
00:11:31.940 --> 00:11:33.650
That's all I have to share.

248
00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:35.940
As far as the outside world's concerned...

249
00:11:35.950 --> 00:11:38.200
this was 2 business people killed in a home robbery.

250
00:11:38.200 --> 00:11:40.160
But how long is that story going to hold?

251
00:11:40.160 --> 00:11:44.250
When it does fall apart. let's look like
we have a fucking clue what we're doing.

252
00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:46.660
That's all.

253
00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:52.460
[DOOR OPENING]

254
00:11:53.920 --> 00:11:54.840
DIANE: Peter.

255
00:11:56.470 --> 00:11:57.340
Yes. ma'am?

256
00:11:59.930 --> 00:12:02.050
What do you think? About Hawkins?

257
00:12:02.050 --> 00:12:04.390
I think he didn't like me sitting in his chair.

258
00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:05.730
Let's double-check his work.

259
00:12:06.230 --> 00:12:09.190
I'm gonna get you the case files for the Campbells from over the years.

260
00:12:09.190 --> 00:12:11.020
I don't think I'm cleared for that.

261
00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:12.190
I'll get you read in.

262
00:12:13.110 --> 00:12:14.770
Okay. What do you want me to look for?

263
00:12:14.780 --> 00:12:15.980
A reason they were targeted...

264
00:12:15.990 --> 00:12:18.240
any connections Hawkins isn't telling us about.

265
00:12:18.820 --> 00:12:19.740
Peter. look...

266
00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:22.200
you've been a good soldier.

267
00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:24.200
Done everything I've asked in Night Action.

268
00:12:24.200 --> 00:12:25.660
I know you're capable of more.

269
00:12:25.660 --> 00:12:28.120
You want to do more. Now I'm asking for more.

270
00:12:28.750 --> 00:12:30.830
We're wading into very murky waters here.

271
00:12:30.830 --> 00:12:34.210
Are you ready to do whatever it takes to get to the bottom of this muck?

272
00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:36.420
To keep Rose Larkin safe?

273
00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:38.090
Absolutely.

274
00:12:39.090 --> 00:12:39.920
Good.

275
00:12:39.930 --> 00:12:41.300
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

276
00:12:42.390 --> 00:12:46.390
The last 12 months. I've been training you
for something. I wasn't sure what for.

277
00:12:47.430 --> 00:12:48.520
But now we know.

278
00:12:48.520 --> 00:12:49.480
It's this.

279
00:12:51.060 --> 00:12:52.190
Time to step up.

280
00:12:55.780 --> 00:12:56.780
Yes. ma'am.

281
00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:59.950
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

282
00:13:00.700 --> 00:13:02.490
[PHONES RINGING]

283
00:13:02.490 --> 00:13:04.030
Hey. Liam.

284
00:13:04.990 --> 00:13:07.330
Anything on that. uh. screenshot I sent you?

285
00:13:07.330 --> 00:13:08.620
Uh. yeah.

286
00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:10.370
Not sure how it helps.

287
00:13:10.960 --> 00:13:13.790
So this is the ring you caught on camera last night.

288
00:13:13.790 --> 00:13:14.710
Yeah.

289
00:13:14.710 --> 00:13:16.050
I found this sigil.

290
00:13:17.250 --> 00:13:18.880
Looks pretty damn close.

291
00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:20.050
PETER: What's it from?

292
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:22.840
Family crest from the Royal House of Yugoslavia.

293
00:13:23.430 --> 00:13:24.720
There's a couple of differences...

294
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:27.260
so I'm guessing the original owner of that ring...

295
00:13:27.260 --> 00:13:30.060
is probably a distant relative to the crown prince.

296
00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:34.150
Can we get anything more on it? Like. uh. maybe check museums...

297
00:13:34.150 --> 00:13:36.310
I don't know. auction houses. anything like that?

298
00:13:36.320 --> 00:13:39.240
Excuse me? You're my boss now. phone boy?

299
00:13:40.530 --> 00:13:41.650
Please?

300
00:13:42.240 --> 00:13:43.740
Look. no-can-do. I'm buried.

301
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:45.410
What's this all about anyway?

302
00:13:45.990 --> 00:13:47.620
Can't tell you. It's above your clearance.

303
00:13:47.620 --> 00:13:48.990
No. seriously.

304
00:13:51.580 --> 00:13:52.410
Seriously?

305
00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:54.920
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

306
00:13:58.500 --> 00:13:59.510
[SCANNER BEEPING]

307
00:14:19.150 --> 00:14:21.150
[POLICE SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

308
00:14:44.340 --> 00:14:46.430
Thank you.
- You're welcome.

309
00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:49.970
What kind of tea is this?
- Pu-erh.

310
00:14:49.970 --> 00:14:51.850
What is that. Chinese?
- I believe so.

311
00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:54.850
It's not gonna make me sleepy. is it? I've got a long night.

312
00:14:54.850 --> 00:14:57.350
No. it's supposed to give you energy. I checked.

313
00:14:57.350 --> 00:14:58.480
Okay. thanks.

314
00:14:58.480 --> 00:15:00.440
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

315
00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:01.610
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

316
00:15:01.610 --> 00:15:03.070
DIANE: <i>Peter. everything okay?</i>

317
00:15:03.070 --> 00:15:07.240
Hey. did you know Hawkins used to be
Emma and Henry Campbell's old FBI handler?

318
00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:08.360
What?
- PETER: <i>Yeah.</i>

319
00:15:08.370 --> 00:15:09.820
It's really hard to find...

320
00:15:09.830 --> 00:15:13.490
but I recognize his initials on some old sign-offs.

321
00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:14.500
These are...

322
00:15:15.080 --> 00:15:16.460
these are going back years.

323
00:15:16.460 --> 00:15:17.420
Shit.

324
00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:19.080
You're sure?

325
00:15:19.080 --> 00:15:21.000
[SIGHING] He didn't tell you he knew them?

326
00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:23.420
No. I knew he worked in counterintelligence...

327
00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:24.840
before his promotion. but...

328
00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:27.510
Fuck a duck.

329
00:15:27.510 --> 00:15:29.510
Shit. I wonder why he didn't tell you.

330
00:15:30.760 --> 00:15:32.470
<i>What else is he hiding. you know?</i>

331
00:15:32.470 --> 00:15:35.890
Separate the cases he oversaw. Have them on my desk in the morning.

332
00:15:36.390 --> 00:15:38.390
And. Peter. keep this between us for now.

333
00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:39.310
Yeah.

334
00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:51.080
[PETER SNIFFLING]

335
00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:53.870
[PHONE RINGING]

336
00:15:57.920 --> 00:15:59.380
Uh. yes. go ahead.

337
00:15:59.880 --> 00:16:01.340
ROSE: <i>Peter. is that you?</i>

338
00:16:02.090 --> 00:16:03.920
Rose?
- ROSE: <i>Yeah.</i>

339
00:16:03.920 --> 00:16:05.710
I can't sleep. and...

340
00:16:07.090 --> 00:16:08.930
um. I remembered the number.

341
00:16:08.930 --> 00:16:11.550
Wait. you...? You remembered this number?

342
00:16:11.550 --> 00:16:13.890
ROSE: <i>Yeah. my brain works like that.</i>
- [PETER CHUCKLING]

343
00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:15.850
I was hoping you would answer.

344
00:16:15.850 --> 00:16:17.640
PETER: Uh. yeah. I mean. it's me.

345
00:16:17.640 --> 00:16:19.480
It's... it's late. Are you okay?

346
00:16:19.480 --> 00:16:20.400
ROSE: <i>No.</i>

347
00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:24.570
I just really needed to hear a voice.
and I... I don't really have anyone. so...

348
00:16:25.480 --> 00:16:27.030
I'm... I'm... I'm here.

349
00:16:28.030 --> 00:16:29.320
Do you know anything more...

350
00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:31.450
<i>about what happened to my aunt and uncle?</i>

351
00:16:31.450 --> 00:16:33.950
We're looking into some things. all right?

352
00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:36.580
Uh. we'll see where it goes.

353
00:16:36.580 --> 00:16:38.620
We're making progress. okay? I promise.

354
00:16:38.620 --> 00:16:41.170
Wait. hang on. Don't you have to keep this line open?

355
00:16:41.170 --> 00:16:42.830
Just in case someone else calls?

356
00:16:42.840 --> 00:16:44.040
You really think it's set up...

357
00:16:44.040 --> 00:16:46.250
so a night Agent in trouble gets a busy signal?

358
00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:48.840
ROSE: <i>Last time I called. you said you had to keep the line open.</i>

359
00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:51.470
Yeah. You didn't have the right answers to the code questions.

360
00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:53.550
So you were just trying to hang up on me.

361
00:16:54.050 --> 00:16:54.970
That's kind of rude.

362
00:16:54.970 --> 00:16:57.020
[CHUCKLING] Sorry. Sorry. okay?

363
00:16:57.020 --> 00:16:59.140
I won't hang up on you tonight. I promise.

364
00:16:59.140 --> 00:17:01.390
You better not. I can be very vindictive.

365
00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:03.110
Yeah. I don't wanna find out.

366
00:17:06.530 --> 00:17:08.110
Can I ask you a question?

367
00:17:09.530 --> 00:17:10.990
PETER: <i>Yeah. Yeah. go ahead.</i>

368
00:17:10.990 --> 00:17:13.070
[ ♪ DRAMATIC MUSIC ♪ ]

369
00:17:13.660 --> 00:17:15.530
Do you know what happens next to me?

370
00:17:16.490 --> 00:17:19.250
[SIGHING] I... I wish I knew. Rose.

371
00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:24.500
[ROSE SIGHING]

372
00:17:33.260 --> 00:17:35.430
It doesn't matter what's in the bag.

373
00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:38.520
[SCOFFING] Yeah. It's obviously worth killing for.

374
00:17:39.020 --> 00:17:40.930
We weren't told we had to kill her.

375
00:17:40.930 --> 00:17:41.940
No.

376
00:17:42.440 --> 00:17:44.980
But faster. safer...

377
00:17:45.480 --> 00:17:47.780
and he didn't tell us not to kill her.

378
00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:54.530
What do you think's in there?

379
00:17:54.530 --> 00:17:57.450
[SIGHING HEAVILY] Stop torturing yourself. okay?

380
00:18:00.160 --> 00:18:01.080
You're right.

381
00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:03.540
I'll just look.

382
00:18:06.630 --> 00:18:07.960
You'll still love me.

383
00:18:14.840 --> 00:18:16.340
What the actual fuck?

384
00:18:16.350 --> 00:18:18.350
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

385
00:18:20.310 --> 00:18:21.480
Satisfied?

386
00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:24.480
It's a nanny cam.

387
00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:27.020
What cords do we need to download what's on here?

388
00:18:27.860 --> 00:18:30.190
Anticipation is always better than the result.

389
00:18:31.280 --> 00:18:32.150
Trust me.

390
00:18:32.150 --> 00:18:33.860
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

391
00:18:33.860 --> 00:18:34.820
Fine.

392
00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:37.320
Uh. it's him.

393
00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:39.370
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

394
00:18:39.370 --> 00:18:40.280
MAN: <i>Yes?</i>

395
00:18:40.290 --> 00:18:41.620
You back in town yet?

396
00:18:41.620 --> 00:18:42.870
We just got here.

397
00:18:42.870 --> 00:18:45.120
MAN#2: I've got new intel on the target.

398
00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:46.790
MAN: <i>Okay. we're ready.</i>

399
00:18:47.420 --> 00:18:48.920
Try to close this time.

400
00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:52.170
There's a good chance she saw you at the house and can ID you.

401
00:18:52.170 --> 00:18:54.880
In case you needed additional incentive.

402
00:18:55.550 --> 00:18:56.550
Who's that?

403
00:18:57.890 --> 00:19:00.760
He's someone with a vested interest in this all working out.

404
00:19:00.760 --> 00:19:03.310
<i>And he's right. the girl's a problem.</i>

405
00:19:03.310 --> 00:19:05.060
Just tell me where she is. okay?

406
00:19:07.060 --> 00:19:07.900
Wait.

407
00:19:11.440 --> 00:19:13.190
[PEN SCRIBBLING]

408
00:19:14.490 --> 00:19:15.320
MAN: Got it.

409
00:19:17.200 --> 00:19:19.240
Well. it's all taken care of.

410
00:19:19.240 --> 00:19:21.620
How long have these people worked for you?

411
00:19:21.620 --> 00:19:23.620
Well. him. over 8 years.

412
00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:24.830
Excellent results.

413
00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:27.330
He brought her in a couple of years ago.

414
00:19:28.330 --> 00:19:29.630
They make a good team.

415
00:19:30.130 --> 00:19:31.920
I mean. no one's asked for a refund yet.

416
00:19:34.050 --> 00:19:35.510
The whole thing makes me ill.

417
00:19:37.180 --> 00:19:39.220
ROSE: <i>Did you always want to be an FBI Agent?</i>

418
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:41.050
PETER: Um. no.

419
00:19:41.050 --> 00:19:42.510
I... I actually...

420
00:19:44.640 --> 00:19:46.230
I wanted to play in the NBA.

421
00:19:46.730 --> 00:19:48.140
Why didn't you?

422
00:19:48.150 --> 00:19:50.230
Because I sucked in college.

423
00:19:50.810 --> 00:19:54.940
If you suck in college. they definitely don't let you play in the pros.

424
00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:58.320
That kind of thinking doesn't fly in Silicon Valley.

425
00:19:58.910 --> 00:20:01.200
<i>If you have a dream. make it happen...</i>

426
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:03.660
no matter how many rules you have to break.

427
00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:05.200
Well. what happened to your dream?

428
00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:08.540
Didn't you have a. uh. business or something like that?

429
00:20:09.040 --> 00:20:09.960
[ROSE EXHALING]

430
00:20:12.630 --> 00:20:13.590
Well. it. um...

431
00:20:15.840 --> 00:20:17.590
It crashed and burned. and...

432
00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:22.640
<i>when I looked around. I was the only one not wearing a parachute.</i>

433
00:20:24.060 --> 00:20:25.520
I was the boss. and I...

434
00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:29.440
I let a friend betray me.

435
00:20:31.980 --> 00:20:33.320
Expensive lesson.

436
00:20:34.610 --> 00:20:35.820
Sorry that happened.

437
00:20:41.410 --> 00:20:42.490
You still there?

438
00:20:44.870 --> 00:20:45.830
Yeah. I...

439
00:20:46.580 --> 00:20:48.210
I think I'm falling asleep.

440
00:20:49.080 --> 00:20:51.580
PETER: <i>That's a good thing. okay? You need sleep.</i>

441
00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:02.050
Peter?

442
00:21:02.050 --> 00:21:04.010
[ ♪ EMOTIONAL MUSIC ♪ ]

443
00:21:04.010 --> 00:21:05.310
PETER: <i>Yeah. what's up?</i>

444
00:21:08.600 --> 00:21:09.890
I'm so lonely...

445
00:21:12.100 --> 00:21:13.110
all the time.

446
00:21:17.530 --> 00:21:19.900
Especially now that they're gone. and...

447
00:21:24.950 --> 00:21:27.040
Can you have breakfast with me tomorrow...

448
00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:29.080
when you finish work?

449
00:21:33.790 --> 00:21:34.880
Yeah. sure.

450
00:21:35.380 --> 00:21:38.510
We have to get room service 'cause they don't let me out of my room.

451
00:21:39.970 --> 00:21:41.220
PETER: <i>I... I figured.</i>

452
00:21:41.220 --> 00:21:42.720
[BOTH LAUGHING]

453
00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:45.890
Sounds good. What. 10:30? Late breakfast?

454
00:21:47.100 --> 00:21:47.970
Okay.

455
00:21:49.100 --> 00:21:50.430
PETER: <i>See ya.</i>
- Bye.

456
00:21:55.150 --> 00:21:56.360
The last one.

457
00:22:02.490 --> 00:22:05.320
Val. can I get some more of that Chinese tea from last night?

458
00:22:05.320 --> 00:22:06.450
Had a real kick to it.

459
00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:09.740
Yes. ma'am. And. heads up. you've got a squatter.

460
00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:11.830
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

461
00:22:12.370 --> 00:22:13.750
[PHONES RINGING]

462
00:22:21.630 --> 00:22:23.050
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGING]

463
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:27.550
Should I charge you rent?

464
00:22:27.550 --> 00:22:29.140
Oh. sorry. ma'am.

465
00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:32.850
I was gonna put those on your desk.
and then laid down on the couch and just...

466
00:22:32.850 --> 00:22:35.770
Find any connections between Hawkins and the Campbells?

467
00:22:35.770 --> 00:22:37.690
Any idea who might have killed them?

468
00:22:37.690 --> 00:22:41.230
Not really. no. But I marked up all their cases that he oversaw.

469
00:22:42.110 --> 00:22:43.990
Thanks. Go get some real sleep.

470
00:22:43.990 --> 00:22:45.740
Can't. I gotta shower...

471
00:22:45.740 --> 00:22:48.280
and. um. I was gonna go see Rose at her hotel.

472
00:22:48.280 --> 00:22:51.160
I promised I'd check up on her.
- Wait. she contacted you again?

473
00:22:51.160 --> 00:22:53.040
Yeah. Yeah. she wants to see me.

474
00:22:53.040 --> 00:22:54.040
Good.

475
00:22:54.710 --> 00:22:57.170
You're forming a connection. Could be valuable.

476
00:22:57.830 --> 00:22:59.500
You need anything before I go?

477
00:22:59.500 --> 00:23:00.420
Go.

478
00:23:01.510 --> 00:23:03.010
Let me know if she opens up.

479
00:23:03.010 --> 00:23:03.920
Yeah.

480
00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:07.840
[ ♪ UPBEAT MUSIC ♪ ]

481
00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:18.400
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

482
00:23:25.150 --> 00:23:26.360
Hey. Excuse me.
- Hi.

483
00:23:26.360 --> 00:23:28.530
Where are the Secret Service Agents that were here?

484
00:23:28.530 --> 00:23:31.200
Oh. uh. they were there earlier.

485
00:23:31.200 --> 00:23:32.160
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]

486
00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:33.580
WOMAN: Whoa.

487
00:23:33.580 --> 00:23:34.660
PETER: No.

488
00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:38.210
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

489
00:24:06.530 --> 00:24:07.360
Rose?

490
00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:09.410
Rose?

491
00:24:10.070 --> 00:24:10.950
[DOOR OPENING]

492
00:24:10.950 --> 00:24:12.120
Rose?
- ROSE: Yeah?

493
00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:13.870
Hey. [PANTING]

494
00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:17.500
ROSE: What's happening?
- We have to get out of here.

495
00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:18.830
How'd you get in here?

496
00:24:18.830 --> 00:24:20.040
They cut the power.

497
00:24:20.040 --> 00:24:23.130
The lock on your door isn't working. We have to go. Come on.

498
00:24:23.130 --> 00:24:25.210
[ ♪ INTENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

499
00:24:33.470 --> 00:24:34.600
Housekeeping.

500
00:24:37.430 --> 00:24:38.350
PETER: Come here.

501
00:24:42.810 --> 00:24:43.770
Housekeeping.

502
00:24:53.530 --> 00:24:54.450
She's not here.

503
00:24:54.450 --> 00:24:56.240
MAN: <i>Copy. I'll meet you in the stairwell.</i>

504
00:25:08.470 --> 00:25:09.300
[DOOR CLOSING]

505
00:25:14.260 --> 00:25:15.470
[ROSE GASPING]

506
00:25:18.140 --> 00:25:19.680
Come with me. Come on. Rose.

507
00:25:24.310 --> 00:25:25.570
[ROSE GRUNTING]
- PETER: Go.

508
00:25:26.320 --> 00:25:27.400
This way. Come on.

509
00:25:45.460 --> 00:25:46.340
You good?

510
00:25:47.500 --> 00:25:48.500
Go. go. go. go.

511
00:25:48.510 --> 00:25:50.010
What happened to the Secret Service?

512
00:25:50.010 --> 00:25:51.770
Someone must've pulled them.
- ROSE: What?

513
00:25:54.930 --> 00:25:56.300
[MAN GRUNTING]

514
00:26:01.350 --> 00:26:02.480
Go!
- ROSE: Okay.

515
00:26:09.280 --> 00:26:10.940
Peter.
- Yeah. I'm here.

516
00:26:19.040 --> 00:26:19.950
Shit.

517
00:26:24.330 --> 00:26:26.420
You're late again. What a surprise.

518
